  planner_response {
    modified_response: "I have completely restructured the application to revolve around the conversational AI experience, shifting it away from a standard SaaS dashboard to a centralized, chat-first paradigm reminiscent of ChatGPT, Claude, and Perplexity.\n\nHere are the key architectural and design updates:\n- **Chat-First Routing**: The `/dashboard` has been entirely removed. When a user logs in or registers, they are now directly routed to `/chat`, which acts as the root of the authenticated application.\n- **ChatGPT-Style Layout Sidebar**: The side navigation has been rebuilt to prioritize conversations. A prominent \"New Thread\" button sits at the top, followed seamlessly by auxiliary platform tools (Alumni Directory, Network Insights), and a dynamic section for recent threads. \n- **Centralized Prompt Hero State**: Instead of looking like a widget, the empty state of `Assistant.tsx` now occupies the full screen with an elegant, centered prompt interface using our `liquid-glass` styling and large Instrument Serif typography to ask: *\342\200\234What do you want to explore?\342\200\235*\n- **Dynamic Input Resizing & Positioning**: The prompt bar behaves natively. It sits centered in the viewport before any messages are sent, and snaps smoothly to the bottom of the screen upon initiating a conversation. The textarea expands dynamically to fit longer thoughts with a clean \'return to send\' micro-interaction.\n\nThe platform now natively feels like a dedicated AI Intelligence assistant rather than standard software. You can interact with it via the updated preview."
